I saw Spiderman 2 last night.....frikin' awesome. *beware of spoilers*. Dock Ock "dies". Harry finds his dads green goblin stuff. MJ finds out that peter parker is spiderman. So does Harry. They set up the possibility for a lot of villains in the next movie. The Lizard, Venom, and the Green Goblin (again). I didn't like this version of Dock Ock very much because the arms controlled him (they had A.I.). Plus he should've had the accent from the 1967 cartoon version. Welcome To Jim's Life.

Hey it's finally back. To all my adoring fans out there who have just been dying to read almost daily updates about my life, here is ur chance (again). A lot of stuff has happened since that fateful day that I deleted my LJ from info, but I'm not going to tell u all of it. You're going to have to guess most of it. Come on, give it a try, let ur imagination go wild. Especially if ur a pretty girl. Eh? eh? heh heh yyeaahhhh........................ Ok i'm sorry, that was weird. Number 1: Star Wars (classic trilogy, fav. one out of them is Return of the Jedi)

Well I'm hungry and noone is online so I'm gonna grab some food. Welcome to Jim's Life.

Well, since I'm really bored and will be for the rest of the day and I have nothing in my life to write about, I just thought I'd ramble on with useless advice to anyone who actually likes to read my Live Journal. My first advice is to never stop making an idiot out of yourself, but don't over do it. If you see a cat and it's hair is all straight and it's tail is poofy don't say "aww look a cat" and then try and pet it because that would be stupid. Don't kick yourself because you might pull a muscle. Sometimes you've just gotta pull down your pants and slide down the ice. Don't threaten someone bigger than you, unless your faster. If you're watching a crappy movie, turn it off, because you could be doing something else. Play video games, trust me you'll regret it if you don't. If you find yourself staring at a girl and she starts looking back, don't do any of the following...fart, sneeze, blow your nose, pick your nose, puke, or scratch yourself. Wear more than one shirt a day, but only one pair of socks (if any at all). Stand in the rain and enjoy it. Don't stand in the rain holding up a big metal pole or you're in for a shock. Don't watch "The Fabulous Life of...." on VH1 because it'll just make you jealous. Don't throw a ripe apple, it's a good thing so eat it. No matter how cool you think it is, it is NOT the best thing since sliced bread. Give M*A*S*H a chance. Do NOT listen to rap, it is senseless rabble about sex and alcohol. Watch cartoons or else you'll lose the grasp on your childhood for the rest of your life. If you're frustrated do NOT punch a hole in the wall, it'll prolly hurt. Don't waste your time reading some pointless live journal that is written by a guy who has too much time on his hands. And last but CERTAINLY not least never EVER ever follow my advice about important stuff. Good thing nothing I said was important. Welcome to Jim's Life.
